HEADWORD: Isochasm
<hw>I"so*chasm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets> +
<ets>chasm</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Phys. Geog.)</fld> <def>A line connecting
places on the earth's surface at which there is the same mean frequency
of auroras.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isochasmic</ent>⟦br⟧
